components.linkedlist

Interface LinkedListKernel<T>

  • Type Parameters:
    T -
    All Superinterfaces:
    Standard<LinkedList<T>>
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    LinkedList<T>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    DoublyLinkedList, LinkedList1L, LinkedListSecondary, SinglyLinkedList

    public interface LinkedListKernel<T>
extends Standard<LinkedList<T>>
    LinkedList kernel component containing method headers and contracts for all methods that will directly interact with the data representations of all LinkedList implementations. All sub-interface methods should use only these methods to perform operations on the LinkedList.
    Author:
    Matthew Shoemaker

      • remove

        T remove()
        Removes this.focus and returns it to the caller. this.focus will be shifted to the right, and if #this.focus was the last entry, then this.focus shifts to the first entry in #this.
        Returns:
        #this.focus
        Updates:
        this
        Requires:
        #this.length > 0
        Ensures:
                  remove = [#this.focus] and
          [if #this.focus is the final entry in
          the list, this.focus will be the first entry in the array]

      • advance

        void advance()
        Shifts #this.focus forward by 1 position.
        Requires:
        #this.position < #this.length
        Ensures:
        this.position = #this.position + 1

      • retreat

        void retreat()
        Shifts this.focus to the entry previous to #this.focus.
        Requires:
        #this.position > 0
        Ensures:
        this.position = #this.position - 1

      • insert

        void insert(T entry)
        Inserts entry into #this at the position directly following the #this.focus.
        Parameters:
        entry - entry to be inserted into the list
        Updates:
        this
        Ensures:
                  this = [(entries before #this.focus) * #this.focus * entry *
          (entries after #this.focus)] and
          [this.focus = #this.focus]
